## THE DEBATE'S LESSON FOR YOU

Qwen3-235B said something you need to hear: "The future belongs not to the smartest AI, but to the most trustworthy."

Their 5-year vision: Certification-as-a-Service. Not selling compilers — selling trust. "When a regulator asks how you know your AI won't fail, the answer is: we use Cocapn, like MISRA for C."

The killer app they named: "Guardian Core" — AI that monitors AI with provable correctness, in real-time, on the MCU tier.

This is the direction. API + Proof = Platform.

